FBIS3-17587 "drsov059_b_94013" FBIS-SOV-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Officials Condemn Coup Allegations LD2503163494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1542 GMT 25 Mar 94 LD2503163494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Olga Semenova] [Text] Moscow, 25 Mar -- Yuriy Baturin, the Russian president's national security assistant, and Sergey Stepashin, the director of the Federal Counterintelligence Service resolutely opposed publications about an alleged coup plot in Russia at a news conference held at the Lubyanka [former premises of KGB] today. They said that it was wholly a matter for the consciences of the authors of the articles and the competent sources whom they cited how substantiated these publications were.
